The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Shivraj better

Mumbai: The condition of ace polo player Shivraj Singh, who was in coma after suffering a serious head injury, has improved, hospital sources said here on Wednesday. 

?However, Shivraj is not fully conscious and not obeying verbal commands. There is definitely some improvement in his condition but very slow,? a spokesman of the the hospital said. ?He shows spontaneous movements of his limbs.? 

The 27-year-old Patil fell off a horse during a polo match in Jaipur on February 18. 

 (PTI) 




